**W3-D4-Django_ORM**

**Today you learn:**
- Create, Read, Update, Delete (CRUD) using ORM
- ORM = writing Python instead of raw SQL to talk to database

---

**1. Create**

```python
from blog.models import Post

Post.objects.create(title="Second Post", content="Learning ORM")  # creates and saves in one line
```

---

**2. Read**

```python
Post.objects.all()                      # get all rows
Post.objects.first()                    # get first row
Post.objects.get(id=1)                  # get one specific row by id - errors if not found or multiple found
Post.objects.filter(title="Second Post") # get rows matching condition - returns a list, even if empty
```

---

**3. Update**

```python
post = Post.objects.get(id=1)
post.title = "Updated Title"   # change the attribute
post.save()                    # save the change back to database
```

```python
Post.objects.filter(id=1).update(title="Bulk Updated")  # updates without fetching object first
```

---

**4. Delete**

```python
post = Post.objects.get(id=2)
post.delete()   # removes that row from database
```

---

**5. Common filter lookups**

```python
Post.objects.filter(title__contains="Post")     # title contains "Post"
Post.objects.filter(id__gt=1)                    # id greater than 1
Post.objects.exclude(id=1)                       # everything except id=1
Post.objects.order_by("-created_at")             # newest first (- means descending)
```

